U.S. Stock-Index Futures Advance as Warren Buffett Eyes More Takeovers

-- B y   M i c h a e l   P .   R e g a n
-- 
2011-02-28T12:38:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/u-s-stock-futures-advance-before-data-on-consumer-spending-home-sales.html
U.S. stock-index futures advanced,
signaling the Standard & Poor’s 500 Index may extend a third
straight monthly gain, before reports on consumer spending,
manufacturing and home sales.  Futures on the Standard & Poor’s 500 Index expiring next
month rose 0.3 percent to 1,322.9 at 7:36 a.m. in  New York . Dow
Jones Industrial Average futures increased 45 points, or 0.4
percent, to 12,155.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Regan at 
 mregan12@bloomberg.net  